<Author>Helen237
<Content>Great !! Excellent small hotel in an excelent location. Booking was simple via email direct to the hotel, got a good rate too. The directions to the hotel were good and we found it no bother from the main Zoo Garten station. The reception staff were friendly and helpful providing maps and directions to the nearest u bahn stations etc. The room was really clean and comfortable, free use of the room safe and great shower. The bed was a bit hard for me and my only dissapointment was the pillows were awful - really small, flat and uncomfy.The hotel is well placed for the KaDeWe dept store, the Ku'Damm and minutes from 2 U bahn stations (Wittenbergplatz and Viktoria Luise Platz). We got a welcome card each in the airport for 16euros each (48 hours) and travelled all over - it was well worth the money.Breakfast was typically continental (No fry up here !!) but the coffee, juice, fruit etc was good - I just can't face ham, cheese and cake for breakfast ?! No tea/coffee tray in room but you could buy them from reception.I'd definitely go here again and recomend to anyone. 
