<Author>aussiepiper
<Content>A Little Worn Around the Edges They say that first impressions count, in which case the worn and dirty polypropylene carpet in the lobby could do well to be replaced. Based on the generally excellent reviews on this web site, we booked our stay directly with the hotel and found their reservations side of things very prompt and efficient. The hotel seems to be part hotel and part permanent accomodation. The lady in the room next to ours had a dog and gave the impression that she was a permanent resident. In any event, the staff were polite and efficient and breakfast excellent. It was good to have muesli on offer with yoghurt and a cooked egg offered as well. Newspapers in English were provided. As other reviewers have pointed out the breakfast room is nicely presented and opens onto a central garden area. The room itself was between two and three star, pretty tired really and the bathroom about 800mm wide, yes, pretty cosy. Our house maid ignored the do not disturb sign every day, which given the night life on offer in Berlin was quite irritating. Also, it would appear that her vacuum cleaner was all noise and no suck, because the carpet in our room appeared not to have been vacuumed for some time, yet the sound of machine could well and truly be heard. The owner of the hotel is a particularly pleasant and polite chap who seemed happy to help on any matter. The last word though must be on price. This is probably good value for money, so taking into account all of my comments above, I wouldn't rule it out on the basis that it offers location and value. 
