<Author>Musclebearnz
<Content>Doesn't get much better than this.. Stayed at the Arco twice in January 2007, first for New Year and then again mid January (and received a discounted rate). We previously used to stay around the corner at a similar type of hotel; this time that hotel was so overpriced so it was our bonus when we found the Arco. The staff are lovely, friendly and helpful. English speaking staff are a bonus. Both rooms we had were big and spacious. Again, like most European hotels, the bathroom was small and definitely only a one person at a time situtation, but the bathrooms were lovely, brand new with all new modern fittings and gleaming white tiles. The breakfast room was big and spacious and the breakfast spread nice, with high quality breads, meats and cheeses. A huge bonus for us, as we run a business and need constant internet access, was the wi-fi throughout the hotel and the charge was a token 3 euro for the whole length of the stay. Unlike some of the horrific charges for internet (we had just left a London hotel who were charging 15 pound a day). The hotel is ideally situated very close to the K-damm. Its also placed just a few minutes walk from 2 U bahn stations, another bonus as we arrived on Easy Jet at Berlin-Schonefeld airport, so we could take the journey on the U-bahn from the airport to the hotel all for 2.5 euro. On the whole, this will be my hotel of choice in Berlin, without question. 
