<Author>Train4Babs
<Content>Nice Hotel in Berlin--Great Value Stayed at the Arco five nights late April 鈥?early May. I agree with all the other reviews. I had a single from for 75 Euros a night. A very good value for Berlin. The hotel is connected to an apartment building which gives it a very residential feel. I had room 403 which was on the top floor and for the most part, very quiet. I didn鈥檛 hear the sound of people taking showers in other rooms which is common in most hotels. There was a dog barking very loudly off and on during the first night (which I also hear all the time back home, so I鈥檓 used to it), but other than that, I was both surprised and pleased that the hotel was so quiet.As typically in many hotels in Europe that have been renovated, the elevator stops half-way between floors, which means you have to drag your bags up half a flight. Then there is an old door that you have to unlock to get access to the hallway. It looked like something out of Cabaret!I wasn鈥檛 crazy about the bathroom, yes it was modern, but it was one of those typically every small European types. You might want to bring your own wash rag as they do not provide them.I also loved the location. It鈥檚 nice to stay in a residential area that with easy access to U-Bahn, KaDeWe and the gay area of Nollendorfplatz. Felt very safe walking alone at night.Front desk staff was friendly, however, they don鈥檛 tend to stay by the desk (they don鈥檛 need to as you are given your own key). One minor complaint: all the guide books I read recommend getting the 鈥淲elcomeCard鈥?which provides 72 free hours on public transportation in Berlin and Brandenburg, as well as reduced or free admission on sightseeing tours, museums and a discount for my favorite, the 鈥淏erlin Walks鈥?tours. When I asked to purchase the Welcome Card at the front desk, they sold me a 鈥淐ity Tour Card鈥?instead. This card offered similar discounts, plus 72 hours of free public transportation in zones A  B, however, the Welcome Card also includes transit in Zone C which covers Potsdam. I didn鈥檛 find the difference between the two cards after I purchased it.Otherwise, I would defiantly stay at the Arco again! 
